{"author":{"id":"138b13306404778af60b1d60d606624fec41556ddac480b2d5f762806ce84fed"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1782958625,"nonce":"EOE5nSpo+O/gfnNP1Up/0rLCihM=","kind":"spec","title":"Private-tier recovery: filtered export/import + local vault — design","content_type":"text/markdown"},{"type":3,"timestamp":1782958625,"nonce":"Y/e8zhAEhTx2R/MEDlqYBlNAjbE=","body":"# Private-tier recovery: filtered export/import + local vault — design\n\n- **Date:** 2026-06-28\n- **Status:** Approved (pending implementation)\n- **Problem:** `private` entries live only in `refs/kref-private/*` in the repo's\n  `.git` and are never pushed (the security invariant). So they are\n  unrecoverable if the repo/disk dies or the dir is `rm -rf`'d. No backup or\n  export exists.\n\n## Verified facts\n\n- Ref layout: entries at `refs/kref-\u003ctier\u003e/\u003cid\u003e`; identities at\n  `refs/identities/\u003cid\u003e`. `git bundle create \u003cfile\u003e \u003ctier refs\u003e \u003cidentity refs\u003e`\n  produces a self-contained bundle (full history → no prerequisites). kref\n  already shells to `git` (`git gc` in `purge`), so shelling to `git bundle` /\n  `git fetch` is consistent.\n- `private` is refused a remote at every layer (`sync.go`). Export/import is a\n  **local** operation (file/stdout, or a local-filesystem vault) and does not\n  violate \"never leaves the machine over the network\".\n\n## Decisions\n\n- **D1 — filtered export.** `kref export [--tier private|personal|shared]…\n  [\u003cfile\u003e|-]` bundles the selected tiers' entry refs **plus all\n  `refs/identities/*`** (so authors resolve on import). Default = all tiers;\n  `--tier` (repeatable) narrows. `-`/no-file ⇒ stdout (pipe-friendly, e.g.\n  `… | sops -e`/`age`). Empty selection (no matching refs) is an error.\n- **D2 — filtered import.** `kref import [--tier …]… \u003cfile|-\u003e` runs\n  `git fetch \u003cbundle\u003e \u003crefspecs\u003e` for the selected tiers + identities. Fresh\n  refs are created (clean restore into a new clone); identical refs are no-ops;\n  a **diverged** (non-fast-forward) ref is **skipped and reported**, never\n  clobbered. (True conflict-free *merge* of diverged private across machines is\n  out of scope for v1 — noted as a limitation; the clean-restore path is the\n  use case.)\n- **D3 — local vault (thin layer over D1/D2).** `kref backup` exports\n  `--tier private` (default) to a kref-managed local file\n  `$XDG_DATA_HOME/kref/\u003crepo-key\u003e/private.bundle` (XDG_DATA_HOME, falling back to\n  `~/.local/share`; **never** cache). `kref restore` imports it back. The path is\n  kref-owned and local-filesystem-only by construction — never a URL — so the\n  invariant holds. `\u003crepo-key\u003e` = a hex hash of the repo's absolute path (stable\n  on the same machine; cross-machine/relocate recovery uses the portable bundle\n  from D1).\n- **D4 — encryption deferred.** kref ships no crypto. The pipe-friendly stdout\n  export composes with SOPS/age today. The native \"encrypt private at rest\"\n  decision is captured in ADR `docs/dev/adr/0001-private-tier-encryption-at-rest.md`\n  (status proposed/deferred).\n\n## Components\n\n- `internal/store/portable.go` (new):\n  - `Export(w io.Writer, tiers []entry.Tier) error` — enumerate refs via\n    `git for-each-ref` for the tiers + identities, `git bundle create` to a temp\n    file, stream into `w`. Error if no refs.\n  - `Import(bundlePath string, tiers []entry.Tier) (ImportResult, error)` —\n    `git fetch \u003cbundlePath\u003e \u003crefspecs\u003e`; parse output for created vs skipped\n    (non-ff) refs; rebuild the in-memory view is unnecessary (refs are read\n    fresh). Returns counts + skipped ids.\n  - `VaultPath() (string, error)` — `$XDG_DATA_HOME|~/.local/share` +\n    `/kref/\u003csha256(abs repo path)[:16]\u003e/private.bundle`.\n- `cmd/kref/commands.go`: `newExportCmd`, `newImportCmd`, `newBackupCmd`,\n  `newRestoreCmd` — all in the `lifecycle` group. `--tier` repeatable string;\n  resolve to `[]entry.Tier` (reuse `parseTier`). `export`/`import` take a path\n  arg (`-`/absent ⇒ std streams). `backup`/`restore` take no path (use the\n  vault). JSON results via `emit`.\n- Docs: README \"Recovering private knowledge\" subsection + command reference;\n  ADR + ADR index.\n\n## Testing (TDD)\n\n- store: round-trip — export `--tier private` from repo A, import into a fresh\n  repo B (no prior private), B sees the private entry with its **original\n  author**; non-selected tiers are absent. all-tiers export/import. diverged ref\n  is skipped (create the same id with different content on both sides). vault\n  path resolves under XDG_DATA_HOME (env-set) and falls back to ~/.local/share.\n- cmd: `kref export --tier private -` emits a non-empty bundle; `kref import`\n  into a fresh clone restores private; `backup`/`restore` round-trip via the\n  vault; empty export errors.\n\n## Out of scope (YAGNI)\n\nContent filters (`--kind`/`--label`) on export, automatic vault syncing (hook),\nconflict-free merge of diverged private, and native encryption (→ ADR)."}]}